class Solution {
    public String strWithout3a3b(int a, int b) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        while (a > 0 || b > 0) {
            if (a > b) {
                if (a >= 2 && b > 0) {
                    sb.append("aab");
                    a -= 2;
                    b -= 1;
                } else {
                    sb.append('a');
                    a -= 1;
                }
            } else {
                if (b >= 2 && a > 0) {
                    sb.append("bba");
                    b -= 2;
                    a -= 1;
                } else {
                    sb.append('b');
                    b -= 1;
                }
            }
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(a + b)
space complexity: O(a + b)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution constructs the required string by iteratively appending 'a' and 'b' characters in a way that avoids 'aaa' and 'bbb' substrings, ensuring the correct count of 'a' and 'b' characters.
